  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000223">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">sistema de proteção catódica</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">cathodic protection system</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CATHODIC PROTECTION SYSTEM&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;CORROSION PROTECTION SYSTEM&gt; using sacrificial anodes or impressed current anodes offering material and giving protection to carbon and low-alloy steel equipment or structures</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A corrosion protection system using sacrificial anodes or impressed current anodes offering material and giving protection to carbon and low-alloy steel equipment or structures.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b412"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(CathodicProtectionSystem(x) ↔ CorrosionProtectionSystem(x) ∧ ∃f(CathodicProtectionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃a(Anode(a) ∧ hasComponentPartAtSomeTime(x,a)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every cathodic protection system is a corrosion protection system that bears a cathodic protection function and has anodes as component parts.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A cathodic protection system is a corrosion protection system that uses electrochemical cathodic protection mechanisms with anodes to prevent corrosion of carbon and low-alloy steel equipment or structures.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um sistema de proteção catódica é um sistema de proteção contra corrosão que usa mecanismos eletroquímicos de proteção catódica com ânodos para prevenir a corrosão de equipamentos ou estruturas de aço carbono e baixa liga.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b72">
    <rdf:first rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000208"/>
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b73"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1684">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/DeformableMaterial"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000366">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">turbine</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">turbina</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every turbine is an assembly that bears an energy extraction function and has component parts including a rotating shaft, fluid interaction blades, casing, and bearing system.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;TURBINE&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;DRIVER(function)&gt; that is a rotary mechanical device that extracts energy from a fluid flow and converts it into useful work</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[DEXPI] An object that is a rotary mechanical device that extracts energy from a fluid flow and converts it into useful work (from ``_).</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that is intended to rotate within a fluid and to transform energy within a fluid into mechanical power.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma turbina é um conjunto que possui uma função de extração de energia e tem eixo rotativo e pás de interação com fluidos que extraem energia de fluidos em movimento e a convertem em trabalho mecânico útil.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A turbine is an assembly that bears an energy extraction function and has rotating shaft and fluid-interacting blades that extract energy from flowing fluids and convert it into useful mechanical work.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b3292"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Turbine(x) ↔ Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(EnergyExtractionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃s(RotatingShaft(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)) ∧ ∃b(FluidInteractionBlades(b) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,b)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b3132">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:intersectionOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b3134"/>
  </rdf:Description>
