  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000158">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[DEXPI] A container intended for storage and/or processing of fluids or solids.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A container intended for storage and/or processing of fluids.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;VESSEL&gt; is a &lt;FLUID CONTAINER&gt;, intended for storage and/or processing of fluids</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">vaso</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">vessel</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every vessel is an assembly that bears a containment function and has a vessel shell and vessel head as component parts at all times.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b3397"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A vessel is an assembly designed to contain fluids or solids for storage and/or processing purposes.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um vaso é um conjunto projetado para conter fluidos ou sólidos para fins de armazenamento e/ou processamento.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Vessel(x) ↔ Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(ContainmentFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃s(VesselShell(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)) ∧ ∃h(VesselHead(h) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,h)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000083">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um MaterialArtifact que possui uma FlowModificationFunction e que é usado como componente em conjuntos de controle de fluxo para alterar as características do fluxo de fluido, como perfil de velocidade, turbulência ou distribuição de pressão.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A MaterialArtifact that bears a FlowModificationFunction and that is used as a component in flow control assemblies to alter the characteristics of fluid flow such as velocity profile, turbulence, or pressure distribution.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1540"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A&lt;FLOW MODIFICATION ACCESSORY&gt; is a &lt;FINAL CONTROL ASSEMBLY COMPONENT&gt; and a &lt;MODIFIER&gt; that is used to modify the characteristics of fluid flow</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flow modification accessory</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">MaterialArtifact que possui uma FlowModificationFunction e</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every flow modification accessory is a MaterialArtifact that bears a FlowModificationFunction and participates in processes that alter fluid flow characteristics.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(FlowModificationAccessory(x) ↔ (MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃f(FlowModificationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
