    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b3338">
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b3333"/>
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b3339"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1855">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FluidConductionFunction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000205">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b7"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b5"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b6"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000144"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (AbsolutePressureTransmitter(x) → PressureTransmitter(x) ∧ ∃y (VacuumReferenceeChamber(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A pressure transmitter where pressure is applied to one side of the sensor while the other side has a vacuum chamber.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;ABSOLUTE PRESSURE TRANSMITTER&gt; is a &lt;PRESSURE TRANSMITTER&gt; and an &lt;ABSOLUTE PRESSURE MEASURING INSTRUMENT&gt;</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An absolute pressure transmitter is a pressure transmitter that has a vacuum reference chamber on one side of the pressure sensor while the other side receives the process pressure.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um transmissor de pressão absoluta é um transmissor de pressão que possui uma câmara de referência de vácuo de um lado do sensor de pressão enquanto o outro lado recebe a pressão do processo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive classification based on vacuum reference chamber configuration. Under Open World Assumption, defining sufficient conditions could lead to unintended classification of complex instruments that contain vacuum chambers but serve different primary functions. The structural differentia is necessary but making it sufficient requires domain expert validation.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">transmissor de pressão absoluta</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">absolute pressure transmitter</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every absolute pressure transmitter is a pressure transmitter that has a vacuum reference chamber as a component part at all times.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1648">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/GaseousFuelPortion"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasInput"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000227">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b476"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ClosureMember"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000370"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">membro de fechamento de válvula de retenção</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">check valve closure member</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(CheckValveClosureMember(x) → MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃y(CheckValve(y) ∧ isComponentPartOf(x,y)) ∧ ∃f(BackflowPreventionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um MaterialArtifact que é uma parte componente de uma válvula de retenção e que possui uma BackflowPreventionFunction, consistindo em um elemento mecânico que previne o refluxo de fluido bloqueando fisicamente o caminho de fluxo quando as condições de pressão indicam potencial refluxo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A MaterialArtifact that is a component part of a check valve and that bears a BackflowPreventionFunction, consisting in a mechanical element that prevents fluid flow reversal by physically blocking the flow path when pressure conditions indicate potential backflow.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CHECK VALVE CLOSURE MEMBER&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;VALVE CLOSURE MEMBER&gt; that is intended to prevent back flow</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every check valve closure member is a MaterialArtifact that is component part of some check valve and bears some BackflowPreventionFunction</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type defined by structural role and mechanism. Under OWA, sufficient conditions would force classification of any artifact with backflow prevention function and check valve association, potentially including hybrid or specialized designs that should not be automatically classified as standard closure members without domain expert validation.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
