  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/InterfacingProcess">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2534"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2535"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a port establishes and maintains a point of interface that enables communication, connection, or interaction between distinct objects or systems.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de interfaceamento</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">interfacing process</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ControlIndicator">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">indicador de controle</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">control indicator</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000087">
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Control valve is a functional type where identity is grounded in the designed function to regulate flow in response to control signals. This functional identity cannot be reduced to structural checklists as the same function can be realized through many different physical mechanisms (ball, butterfly, globe, gate, etc.). The presence of actuator and flow control element are necessary but not sufficient - the key is the integration for automated flow modulation.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b663"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000077"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b664"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">control valve</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula de controle</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[isa5_1] a device, other than a common, hand-actuated process block valve or self-actuated check valve, that directly manipulates the flow of one or more fluid process streams.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A valve that controls a process variable, such as pressure, flow or temperature, by modulating its opening in response to a signal from a controller.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] Modulating valve that controls either the flow rate, liquid level, or pressure in process equipment. In the latter case, it is often referred to as a (pressure) regulator.                   (Note - Typically, high pressure gas from the pipeline is used as the supply medium needed to energize the valve actuator.) https://www.ipieca.org/resources/methane-emissions-glossary</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CONTROL VALVE&gt; is a &lt;VALVE&gt; and an &lt;FINAL CONTROL FUNCTION&gt;, operated by an &lt;ACTUATOR&gt; that can be used to modify the fluid flow rate in response to a signal from a &lt;CONTROLLER&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A valve that can be used to modify (regulate) the fluid flow rate in a process control system. It usually includes an actuator, which responds to a signal from the controlling system and changes the position of the flow controlling element in the valve.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A valve that can be used to modify (regulate)  the fluid flow rate in a process control system. It usually includes an actuator, which responds to a signal from the controlling system and changes the position of the flow controlling element in the valve.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula de controle é uma válvula que é equipada com um atuador e regula a vazão de fluido em resposta a sinais de controle de um sistema de controle de processo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A control valve is a valve that is equipped with an actuator and regulates fluid flow rate in response to control signals from a process control system.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every control valve is a valve that has an actuator as component part and has a flow control function and participates in flow control processes by receiving control signals and modulating fluid flow.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000087"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">ControlValve(x) → Valve(x) ∧ ∃a(Actuator(a) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,a)) ∧ ∃f(FlowControlFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∀p(participatesIn(x,p) ∧ FlowControlProcess(p) → ∃s(ControlSignal(s) ∧ hasInput(p,s)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
