  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000346">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every shaft is an assembly that transmits power through rotation and has shaft keys, shaft seals, and shaft sleeves as essential components.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2914"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2917"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2916"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2915"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">shaft</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">eixo</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive classification based on physical structure. Under OWA, sufficient conditions for shaft identity could lead to false positives - any assembly with a shaft key and rotational motion might be classified as a shaft rather than a more specific equipment type that contains a shaft. The structural differentia provides necessary conditions while allowing domain experts to validate sufficiency.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um Assembly que porta uma PowerTransmissionFunction e que possui partes componentes incluindo chavetas de eixo para transmissão de torque e vedações de eixo para prevenção de vazamento, servindo como o elemento rotativo central em máquinas rotativas.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An Assembly that bears a PowerTransmissionFunction and that has component parts including shaft keys for torque transmission and shaft seals for leakage prevention, serving as the core rotating element in rotating machinery.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Shaft(x) → Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(PowerTransmissionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃k(ShaftKey(k) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,k)) ∧ ∃s(ShaftSeal(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)) ∧ ∃l(ShaftSleeve(l) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,l)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SHAFT&gt; is an &lt;ENGINE COMPONENT&gt; that is the core rotating element on which the rotating parts are mounted and through which energy is either transmitted from the prime mover or generated in case of a driver.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b3264">
