  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000073">
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b602"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that is driven by a prime mover by which energy is either constantly or periodically added to an amount of gas in order to increase its pressure.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A 'gas pressure increase device' and an 'artefact' that is driven by a prime mover by which energy is either constantly or periodically added to an amount of gas in order to increase its pressure.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;COMPRESSOR&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that has the capability of &lt;COMPRESSING&gt; a &lt;GAS&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A type of pump that increases the pressure of gas. Commonly used as a production rate increaser by increasing the gas pressure delivered from low pressure gas wells to enter the pipe line. The intake into the compressor lowers the wellhead pressure creating a larger drawdown.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A device that raises the pressure of air or natural gas.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[DEXPI] A machine that has the capability of compressing a gas.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Compressor(x) ↔ Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(CompressionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A compressor is an assembly that bears the designed function of compressing gases by adding mechanical energy to increase their pressure.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um compressor é um conjunto que possui a função projetada de comprimir gases através da adição de energia mecânica para aumentar sua pressão.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">compressor</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">compressor</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every compressor is an assembly that bears a compression function and has component parts including a compressor casing, compression element, gas inlet, and gas outlet.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000124">
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Heater(x) ↔ Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(HeatingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1832"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">heater</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">aquecedor</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every heater is an assembly that bears a heating function and has heating elements and housing as component parts at all times</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A heater is an assembly that bears a heating function to add thermal energy to a medium.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um aquecedor é um conjunto que possui uma função de aquecimento para adicionar energia térmica a um meio.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] Equipment that transfers heat to the produced gas stream.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;HEATER&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that has the capability of &lt;HEATING&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[DEXPI] An apparatus or machine that has the capability of heating.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2358">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PigReceivingProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000128">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A level element is an instrument that bears a level detection function for determining fluid level in a vessel or container.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um elemento de nível é um instrumento que possui uma função de detecção de nível para determinar o nível de fluido em um vaso ou recipiente.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">level element</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">elemento de nível</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (LevelElement(x) ↔ Detector(x) ∧ ∃f(LevelDetectionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A detecting element that is intended to determine a level.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2082"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every level element is a detector that has the function to detect fluid level</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b3404">
    <rdf:rest rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#nil"/>
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b3400"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b731">
    <rdf:first rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000236"/>
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b732"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1714">
    <rdf:first rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000100"/>
    <rdf:rest rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#nil"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000123">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1771"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000077"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1770"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">globe valve</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula globo</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A valve that is a valve where the closure member is a disc or piston operating with linear motion normal to the flat or shaped seat.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;GLOBE VALVE&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;VALVE&gt; where the closure member is a disc or piston operating with linear motion normal to the flat or shaped seat</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A valve whose closure element is a flat disc or conical plug sealing on a seat that is usually parallel to the flow axis.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A valve that is a valve where the closure member is a disc or piston operating with linear motion normal to the flat or shaped seat.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every globe valve is a valve that has as component part at all times a linear motion closure and a normal seat.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions for this constructive type. Under OWA, making the structural differentia sufficient could force classification of specialized equipment containing linear motion closures (like complex multi-way valves or custom manifolds) as standard globe valves when they may warrant distinct maintenance categories.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula globo é uma válvula caracterizada por um elemento de fechamento (disco ou tampão) que opera com movimento linear perpendicular a uma sede orientada normal ao caminho do fluxo do fluido.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A globe valve is a valve characterized by a closure member (disc or plug) that operates with linear motion perpendicular to a seat that is oriented normal to the fluid flow path.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(GlobeValve(x) → Valve(x) ∧ ∃y,z(hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y) ∧ LinearMotionClosure(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,z) ∧ NormalSeat(z)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2547">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PositionSensor"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/RapidDepressurizationProcess">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">rapid depressurization process</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de despressurização rápida</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b262"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b260"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b261"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1620">
    <owl:members rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1621"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#AllDisjointClasses"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ActuatingMechanism">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">actuating mechanism</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">mecanismo de atuação</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000117">
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every flow indicator is an instrument that bears a flow indication function and has a flow measuring element and display element as component parts.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1497"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um indicador de fluxo é um indicador projetado para indicar taxas de fluxo usando um elemento de medição de fluxo e elemento de exibição.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A flow indicator is an indicator that is designed to indicate flow rates using a flow measuring element and display element.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (FlowIndicator(x) ↔ (Instrument(x) ∧ ∃f(FlowIndicationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃e(FlowMeasuringElement(e) ∧ hasComponentPartAtSomeTime(x,e)) ∧ ∃d(DisplayElement(d) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,d))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">indicador de fluxo</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flow indicator</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FLOW INDICATOR&gt; is an &lt;INSTRUMENTATION ITEM&gt; and a &lt;FLOW MEASURING INSTRUMENT&gt; and a &lt;INDICATOR&gt; that, using a &lt;FLOW MEASURING ELEMENT&gt;, is specially and exclusively designed for &lt;INDICATING&gt; a &lt;FLOW RATE&gt;</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2094">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasInput"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FluidPortion"/>
