  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/SealingFunction">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">sealing function</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de vedação</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1679"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2880"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2879"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/DesignedFunction"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1678"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in a SealingProcess and that consists in providing a tight interface against which a closure element bears to prevent fluid leakage through a valve.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/CircuitProtectionFunction">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de proteção de circuito</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">circuit protection function</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/DesignedFunction"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b554"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1609"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b555"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1608"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/BottomOutlet">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">bottom outlet</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">saída de fundo</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ElectricEnergyGenerationProcess">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">electric energy generation process</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de geração de energia elétrica</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1164"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1165"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000249">
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(DiaphragmPump(x) → (ReciprocatingPump(x) ∧ ∃d(FlexibleDiaphragm(d) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,d)) ∧ ∃p(DiaphragmSealing(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000337"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b936"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b937"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b938"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions because this is a constructive type defined by physical mechanism. Under OWA, any pump with a flexible diaphragm component could be classified as a diaphragm pump, but there may be hybrid or specialized equipment containing diaphragms that should not be automatically classified into this maintenance category.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A reciprocating pump intended to pump a liquid with a small capacity. This is done by means of thin flexible diaphragms to seal pumped fluid from leakage to atmosphere.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DIAPHRAGM PUMP&gt; is a &lt;RECIPROCATING PUMP&gt; intended to pump a liquid with a small capacity. This is done by means of thin flexible diaphragms to seal pumped fluid from leakage to atmosphere; flow rate is achieved through reciprocatory motion of the diaphragm</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma bomba de diafragma é uma bomba alternativa que usa diafragmas flexíveis para deslocar líquido e selar o fluido bombeado contra vazamento atmosférico.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A diaphragm pump is a reciprocating pump that uses flexible diaphragms to displace liquid and seal the pumped fluid from atmospheric leakage.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">bomba de diafragma</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">diaphragm pump</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every diaphragm pump is a reciprocating pump that has flexible diaphragm as component part at all times and participates in diaphragm sealing.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000257">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DRIVE SHAFT&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and an &lt;ENERGY TRANSFERRER&gt; that is a shaft used to transfer rotational power from a prime driver to several individual machines by use of drive belts and pulley wheels</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A drive shaft is an Assembly that bears a PowerTransmissionFunction and consists in a shaft-based system used to transfer rotational mechanical energy from a prime mover to multiple driven machines.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um eixo de transmissão é um Assembly que possui uma PowerTransmissionFunction e consiste em um sistema baseado em eixo usado para transferir energia mecânica rotacional de um motor primário para múltiplas máquinas acionadas.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">DriveShaft ≡ Assembly ⊓ ∃bearerOf.PowerTransmissionFunction ⊓ ∃participatesIn.RotationalPowerTransferProcess</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (DriveShaft(x) ↔ (Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(PowerTransmissionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃p(RotationalPowerTransferProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1108"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">drive shaft</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">eixo de transmissão</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000269">
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(FinnedTubeHeatExchanger(x) → HeatExchanger(x) ∧ ∃y(FinnedTube(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um trocador de calor de tubos aletados é um trocador de calor que possui tubos aletados como mecanismo primário de aumento da superfície de transferência de calor.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A finned tube heat exchanger is a heat exchanger that has finned tubes as the primary heat transfer surface enhancement mechanism.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1333"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000092"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1332"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1335"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1334"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A heat exchanger that has finned tubes.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FINNED TUBE HEAT EXCHANGER&gt; is an &lt;INDIRECT CONTACT HEAT EXCHANGER&gt; that has finned tubes</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A heat exchange that has finned tubes.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">finned tube heat exchanger</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">trocador de calor de tubos aletados</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions for this constructive type. While finned tubes are the defining structural feature, making sufficient conditions (equivalence) under Open World Assumption could lead to false positives where any assembly containing finned tubes would be classified as this specific heat exchanger type, including complex multi-function equipment or specialized hybrid systems.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every finned tube heat exchanger is a heat exchanger that has finned tubes as component parts at all times</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/HydraulicPumpingProcess">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1916"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1915"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PumpingProcess"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1914"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de bombeamento hidráulico</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">hydraulic pumping process</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/InLineFilter">
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every in-line filter is a filter that has an in-line installation method and is supported by connected equipment.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An in-line filter is a filter that is installed directly within a fluid line and supported by connected piping or equipment, designed to remove particles or contaminants from fluid streams during normal flow operations.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um filtro em linha é um filtro que é instalado diretamente dentro de uma linha de fluido e suportado por tubulações ou equipamentos conectados, projetado para remover partículas ou contaminantes de correntes de fluido durante operações normais de fluxo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">filtro em linha</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">in line filter</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (InLineFilter(x) → Filter(x) ∧ ∃m,e (InLineInstallation(m) ∧ ConnectedEquipment(e) ∧ hasInstallationMethod(x,m) ∧ supportedBy(x,e)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000081"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1962"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1963"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions because this is a constructive type defined by physical installation configuration. Under OWA, any filter with in-line connections and piping support could be classified as in-line filter, but specialized hybrid equipment or custom installations might have these features without belonging to the standard in-line filter maintenance category. Starting with necessary conditions protects against false positives.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;IN-LINE FILTER&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;FILTER&gt; that is intended to be supported by connected equipment. Typically supported by piping</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FlexibleElement">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flexible element</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">elemento flexível</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
