  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000074">
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">ShellAndTubeHeatExchanger(x) → HeatExchanger(x) ∧ ∃tb(TubeBundle(tb) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,tb)) ∧ ∃s(Shell(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s) ∧ spatiallyContains(s,tb))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2957"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000092"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2959"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2956"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2958"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SHELL AND TUBE HEAT EXCHANGER&gt; is a &lt;TUBULAR HEAT EXCHANGER&gt; in which a tube bundle is surrounded by a shell</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A tubular heat exchanger in which a tube bundle is surrounded by a shell.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A tubular heat exchanger in which a tube bundle is surrounded by a shell.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">trocador de calor de casco e tubos</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">shell and tube heat exchanger</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A shell and tube heat exchanger is a heat exchanger that has a tube bundle spatially contained within a surrounding shell.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um trocador de calor de casco e tubos é um trocador de calor que possui um feixe de tubos contido espacialmente dentro de um casco envolvente.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every shell and tube heat exchanger is a heat exchanger that has a tube bundle as component part and has a shell as component part, where the tube bundle is spatially contained within the shell.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions for this constructive type to avoid false positives under OWA. Any equipment with a shell and tube bundle could theoretically be classified as a standard shell-and-tube heat exchanger, but specialized variants (like graphite shell-and-tube or custom multi-stream designs) should not be automatically forced into this maintenance category without domain expert validation.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ElectricalConductionFunction">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1199"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b3087"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1200"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b3086"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/DesignedFunction"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">electrical conduction function</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de condução elétrica</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in an ElectricalConductionProcess and that consists in providing a pathway for electrical current to pass from one electrical apparatus to another, enabling electrical connectivity and power or signal transmission.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in an ElectricalConductionProcess and that consists in providing a conductive pathway for electrical current within an electrical contact assembly.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/TemperatureMeasurementAndTransmissionProcess">
