  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000153">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula de retenção basculante</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">swing check valve</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b3084"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b3085"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000103"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A check valve in which the closure element is a hinged clapper that swings or rotates about a supporting shaft.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SWING CHECK VALVE&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;CHECK VALVE&gt; where the closure member is a disc which swings freely on a hinge and which opens automatically when flow is established and closes automatically when flow ceases or is reversed</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A check valve that is a check valve where the closure member is a disc which swings freely on a hinge and which opens automatically when flow is established and closes automatically when flow ceases or is reversed.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A check valve that is a check valve where the closure member is a disc which swings freely on a hinge and which opens automatically when flow is established and closes automatically when flow ceases or is reversed.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A swing check valve is a check valve that has a closure member consisting of a disc which swings freely on a hinge mechanism and opens automatically when flow is established and closes automatically when flow ceases or reverses.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula de retenção basculante é uma válvula de retenção que possui um elemento de fechamento consistindo de um disco que gira livremente em um mecanismo de dobradiça e abre automaticamente quando o fluxo é estabelecido e fecha automaticamente quando o fluxo cessa ou se inverte.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(SwingCheckValve(x) → CheckValve(x) ∧ ∃d(HingedDisc(d) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,d)) ∧ ∃a(SwingArm(a) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,a)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions for this constructive type to avoid false positives under OWA. Any artifact with a hinged disc mechanism should not automatically be classified as a swing check valve without domain expert validation, as specialized equipment may contain swing mechanisms but serve different primary functions.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every swing check valve is a check valve that has a hinged disc as component part and has a swing arm as component part</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1765">
