  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000222">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] One of several strings of steel pipe in a well design that, together with cement, forms a barrier to fluid movement along the drilled hole. It is commonly at least partly cemented in the wellbore.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] Large-diameter pipe lowered into an openhole and cemented in place.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CASING&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and an &lt;ENCLOSURE&gt; that is the stationary enclosure of a machine intended to contain a fluid and equipment internals</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] An enclosure that can maintain a pressure difference.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um casing é um conjunto que fornece invólucro estrutural com capacidade de contenção de pressão, caracterizado por paredes que separam componentes internos ou fluidos do ambiente externo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A casing is an assembly that provides structural enclosure with pressure containment capability, characterized by walls that separate internal components or fluids from the external environment.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000222"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every casing is an assembly that has an enclosure function and has component part some casing wall and has function some pressure containment function.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Casing(x) → Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(EnclosureFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃w(CasingWall(w) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,w)) ∧ ∃p(PressureContainmentFunction(p) ∧ hasFunction(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b405"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b404"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b406"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive classification based on structural configuration. Under OWA, sufficient conditions for enclosure structure could lead to over-classification of complex assemblies that contain enclosure elements but serve different primary functions (e.g., pressure vessels, housings, containers).</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">casing</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">casing</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
