  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000298">
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every hydraulic actuator is an actuator that has hydraulic fluid portion as input and participates in hydraulic to mechanical energy conversion process.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1892"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1891"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1890"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000207"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(HydraulicActuator(x) → Actuator(x) ∧ ∃y(HydraulicFluidPortion(y) ∧ hasInput(x,y)) ∧ ∃z(HydraulicToMechanicalEnergyConversionProcess(z) ∧ participatesIn(x,z)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A hydraulic actuator is an actuator that converts hydraulic fluid pressure into mechanical motion through hydraulic power transmission.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um atuador hidráulico é um atuador que converte pressão de fluido hidráulico em movimento mecânico através de transmissão de potência hidráulica.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;HYDRAULIC ACTUATOR&gt; is an &lt;INSTRUMENTATION ITEM&gt; and a &lt;CONTROLLED ACTUATOR&gt; and a &lt;HYDRAULICALLY ACTUATED ARTEFACT&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] An actuator intended to be operated by hydraulic power.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] An actuator intended to be operated by hydraulic power.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">atuador hidráulico</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">hydraulic actuator</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive classification based on hydraulic power source. Under Open World Assumption, asserting equivalence could incorrectly classify complex hydraulic-mechanical hybrid systems or specialized equipment containing hydraulic actuator components as standard hydraulic actuators.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b881">
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b882"/>
    <rdf:first rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000245"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000277">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FLEXIBLE RISER&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;RISER&gt; that is a flexible vertical or near vertical pipe for the flow of liquid or gas between the seabed and the surface</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A flexible vertical or near vertical pipe for the flow of liquid or gas between the seabed and the surface.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(FlexibleRiser(x) → Riser(x) ∧ ∃q(FlexibleProperty(q) ∧ hasQuality(x,q)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1483"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1482"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1481"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000339"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every flexible riser is a riser that has a flexible property</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flexible riser</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">riser flexível</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um riser flexível é um riser que possui construção de material flexível permitindo condução de fluido vertical ou quase vertical entre o fundo do mar e a superfície, acomodando o movimento da embarcação.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A flexible riser is a riser that has flexible material construction allowing vertical or near-vertical fluid conduction between seabed and surface while accommodating vessel movement.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type where flexibility is a material/structural property. Under OWA, asserting equivalence would force any pipe with flexible qualities to be classified as a flexible riser, even if it serves different functions or has different deployment contexts. Starting with necessary conditions protects against false positives.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b3014">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000059"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasSpecifiedOutput"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000349">
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type based on physical structure. Under OWA, defining sufficient conditions based solely on having a grooved rim could lead to false positives where other grooved mechanical elements (like timing belt pulleys with different design intents) are automatically classified as sheaves. The structural differentia provides necessary conditions while allowing domain experts to confirm sufficient conditions.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SHEAVE&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;WHEEL&gt; which is grooved for use with vee-belts, ropes, round belts, wire or pipe</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A wheel which is grooved for use with vee-belts, ropes, round belts, wire or pipe.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] In oilfield usage, the term usually refers to either the pulleys permanently mounted on the top of the rig (the crown blocks), or the pulleys used for running wireline tools into the wellbore.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A grooved pulley.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A sheave is a material artifact that is a grooved wheel designed to transmit mechanical power through interface with belts, ropes, wires, or pipes.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma polia é um artefato material que é uma roda sulcada projetada para transmitir energia mecânica através da interface com correias, cordas, cabos ou tubos.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">polia</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">sheave</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2949"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2950"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2951"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Sheave(x) → MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃y(GroovedRim(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y)) ∧ ∃f(PowerTransmissionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every sheave is a material artifact that has a grooved rim as component part and bears a power transmission function.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1311">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasSpecifiedOutput"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FluidPortion"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1453">
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FlashVaporizationProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000331">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2572"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2573"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000072"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2571"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every positive displacement pump is a pump that has a displacement mechanism as component part at all times and participates in positive displacement processes.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">bomba de deslocamento positivo</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">positive displacement pump</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A type of fluid pump in which the displacement volume of the pump is fixed for each rotation of the pump.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;POSITIVE DISPLACEMENT PUMP&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;PUMP&gt; intended to transport liquid through the reciprocating or rotary displacement principle and with either fixed or adjustable volume flow rates. NOTE - Combine with either BARE PUMP or PUMP SYSTEM,</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma bomba de deslocamento positivo é uma bomba que transporta líquido através do princípio de deslocamento alternativo ou rotativo com volume de deslocamento fixo por ciclo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A positive displacement pump is a pump that transports liquid through reciprocating or rotary displacement principle with fixed displacement volume per cycle.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type defined by physical mechanism. Under OWA, sufficient conditions based on displacement mechanism alone could lead to false positives where specialized equipment containing displacement elements might be incorrectly classified as standard positive displacement pumps.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(PositiveDisplacementPump(x) → Pump(x) ∧ ∃y(DisplacementMechanism(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y)) ∧ ∃z(PositiveDisplacementProcess(z) ∧ participatesIn(x,z)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
