  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000287">
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every gasket is a material artifact that has component part some deformable material and bears some sealing function and has property some closed loop geometry.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A seal that is one or more closed loops of deformable material used between mating surfaces which have only very limited movement relative to each other.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A seal that is one or more closed loops of deformable material used between mating surfaces which have only very limited movement relative to each other.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] Any of several replaceable seals in equipment or tools.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;GASKET&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;SEAL&gt; that is one or more closed loops of deformable material used between mating surfaces which have only very limited movement relative to each other</skos:definition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1682"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Gasket(x) ↔ MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃f(SealingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃m(DeformableMaterial(m) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,m)) ∧ ∃g(ClosedLoopGeometry(g) ∧ hasProperty(x,g)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma junta é um artefato material feito de material deformável arranjado em loops fechados que possui uma função de vedação para prevenir vazamentos entre superfícies de acoplamento com movimento relativo limitado.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A gasket is a material artifact made of deformable material arranged in closed loops that bears a sealing function to prevent leakage between mating surfaces with limited relative movement.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">gasket</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">junta</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000075">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um absorvedor é um vaso de pressão que realiza uma função de absorção para transferência seletiva de massa de componentes de uma mistura fluida para uma fase absorvente.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An absorber is a pressure vessel that realizes an absorption function for selective mass transfer of components from a fluid mixture into an absorbent phase.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">absorber</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">absorvedor</rdfs:label>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b14"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Absorber(x) ↔ (Separator(x) ∧ ∃f(AbsorptionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A functional object that absorbs.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;ABSORBER&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that has a capability of &lt;ABSORBING&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A vertical, cylindrical vessel that recovers heavier (longer carbon chain) hydrocarbons from a mixture of lighter hydrocarbons.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every absorber is a separator that has the function to absorb specific components from fluid mixtures through mass transfer to an absorbent phase</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
