  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000311">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A fluid container that contains a chamber with several openings.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] An arrangement of piping or valves designed to control, distribute and typically monitor fluid flow.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;MANIFOLD&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;FLUID CONDUCTOR&gt; that is an arrangement of piping or valves designed to control, distribute and typically monitor fluid flow</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A junction or center for connecting several pipes and selectively routing the flow.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that contains a chamber with several openings.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] IMF purpose entity</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every manifold is an assembly that has-component-part-at-all-times some chamber and has-component-part-at-all-times some multiple fluid openings and bears some fluid distribution function.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">manifold</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">manifold</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">As a constructive type, manifolds are defined by structural configuration. Under OWA, asserting equivalence would force any assembly with a chamber and multiple openings to be classified as a manifold, potentially misclassifying complex equipment with manifold-like components (e.g., turbine casings, complex valves). Starting with necessary conditions protects against false positives.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2204"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2203"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2205"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um manifold é um conjunto que possui uma câmara com múltiplas aberturas de fluido projetada para distribuir o fluxo de fluido.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A manifold is an assembly that has a chamber with multiple fluid openings designed to distribute fluid flow.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Manifold(x) → Assembly(x) ∧ ∃c(Chamber(c) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,c)) ∧ ∃o(MultipleFluidOpenings(o) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,o)) ∧ ∃f(FluidDistributionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000339">
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every riser is a pipe that has vertical orientation and participates in upward flow processes.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;RISER&gt; is a &lt;FLUID CONDUCTOR&gt; and a &lt;FLUID TRANSPORTER&gt; that is a vertical or near vertical pipe for the upward flow of liquid or gas</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that is a vertical or near vertical pipe for the upward flow of liquid or gas.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] Pipe through which liquid travels upward.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A physical object that is a vertical or near vertical pipe for the upward flow of liquid or gas.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Riser(x) → Pipe(x) ∧ ∃q(VerticalOrientation(q) ∧ hasQuality(x,q)) ∧ ∃p(UpwardFlowProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um riser é um tubo que tem orientação vertical ou quase vertical e é projetado para o fluxo ascendente de líquido ou gás.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A riser is a pipe that has vertical or near-vertical orientation and is designed for the upward flow of liquid or gas.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2770"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2769"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000321"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">riser</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">riser</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions because this is a constructive type defined by physical configuration. Under OWA, any pipe with vertical orientation and upward flow could be forced into this category, including specialized equipment that should not be classified as standard risers (e.g., reactor internals, distillation column internals). Starting with necessary conditions protects against false positives.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/SubsurfaceResourceInteractionProcess">
