  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000263">
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">ElectricalConnector ≡ ElectricalEquipment ⊓ ∃bearerOf.ElectricalConnectionFunction</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um conector elétrico é um equipamento elétrico que possui uma função de conexão elétrica e que mantém contato elétrico íntimo entre duas ou mais partes de condutor elétrico para permitir fluxo contínuo de corrente.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An electrical connector is an electrical equipment that bears an electrical connection function and that maintains intimate electrical contact between two or more electrical conductor parts to enable continuous current flow.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A connector for holding two parts of a conductor in intimate contact.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;ELECTRICAL CONNECTOR&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and an &lt;CONNECTOR&gt; for holding two parts of &lt;ELECTRICAL CONDUCTOR&gt; in intimate contact</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">conector elétrico</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">electrical connector</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(ElectricalConnector(x) ↔ ElectricalEquipment(x) ∧ ∃f(ElectricalConnectionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1211"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1413">
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1408"/>
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1414"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000283">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1628"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1631"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1630"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1629"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1632"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000084"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type defined by cyclonic mechanism. Under Open World Assumption, any device with cyclonic flow chamber could be falsely classified as gas cyclone separator, including specialized multi-stage cyclones or hybrid separator designs that should not be forced into this standard maintenance category.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A static device generating centrifugal force from an incoming flow which separates solid or liquids from a gas of a different density.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um separador ciclônico de gás é um separador que separa partículas sólidas ou gotículas líquidas do gás usando força centrífuga gerada pela geometria de fluxo ciclônico.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A gas cyclone separator is a separator that separates solid particles or liquid droplets from gas using centrifugal force generated by cyclonic flow geometry.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">separador ciclônico de gás</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">gas cyclone separator</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every gas cyclone separator is a separator that has a cyclonic flow chamber as component part and participates in centrifugal separation processes.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (GasCycloneSeparator(x) → Separator(x) ∧ ∃y(CyclonicFlowChamber(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y)) ∧ ∃z(CentrifugalSeparationProcess(z) ∧ participatesIn(x,z)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
