  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ElectricalConnectionProcess">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1209"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1210"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de conexão elétrica</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">electrical connection process</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which two or more electrical conductor parts are held in intimate contact by an electrical connector, resulting in a conductive path that enables electrical current flow through the connection.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000084">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">separator</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">separador</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A cylindrical or spherical vessel used to separate oil, gas and water from the total fluid stream produced by a well. Separators can be either horizontal or vertical.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SEPARATOR&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that has a capability of &lt;SEPARATING&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A production treating vessel designed to facilitate the separation of gas, oil, and/or water from a produced fluid stream.                  Also                  The term separator in oilfield terminology designates a pressure vessel used for separating well fluids produced from oil and gas wells into gaseous and liquid components. A separator for petroleum production is a large vessel designed to separate production fluids into their constituent components of oil, gas and water. Separators include related process control components, like pneumatic controllers, and may contain a heater to enhance phase separation or prevent freezing during cold weather. A separating vessel may be referred to in the following ways: Oil and gas separator, Separator, Stage separator, Trap, Knockout vessel (Knockout drum, knockout trap, water knockout, or liquid knockout), Flash chamber (flash vessel or flash trap), Expansion separator or expansion vessel, Scrubber (gas scrubber), Filter (gas filter). These separating vessels are normally used on a producing lease or platform near the wellhead, manifold, or tank battery to separate fluids produced from oil and gas wells into oil and gas or liquid and gas. https://www.mines.edu/global-energy-future/wp-content/uploads/sites/361/2024/05/Payne_Institute_Responsible_Gas_Glossary_of_Terminology_211022_version-9.pdf</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A 'device' intended to separate different types of substances.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Separator(x) ↔ (Vessel(x) ∧ ∃f (SeparationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2894"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every separator is a vessel that has the function of separating mixed fluid streams into distinct phases or components.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um separador é um vaso que possui uma FunçãoDeSeparação - projetado para separar diferentes substâncias ou fases de uma corrente fluida mista em correntes de saída distintas.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A separator is a vessel that bears a SeparationFunction - designed to separate different substances or phases from a mixed fluid stream into distinct output streams.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000102">
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every centrifugal pump is a pump that has a centrifugal impeller as component part at all times and has a volute casing as component part at all times.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(CentrifugalPump(x) → Pump(x) ∧ ∃y(CentrifugalImpeller(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y)) ∧ ∃z(VoluteCasing(z) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,z)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma bomba centrífuga é uma bomba que usa força centrífuga gerada por impulsores rotativos com pás para aumentar a pressão do fluido através de uma carcaça voluta.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A centrifugal pump is a pump that uses centrifugal force generated by rotating impellers with vanes to increase fluid pressure through a volute casing.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000102"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">bomba centrífuga</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">centrifugal pump</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A type of pump commonly used in the handling and mixing of oilfield fluids.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] Pump with an impeller or rotor that spins in a housing and the drag forces on the fluids cause them to flow.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A dynamic pump utilizing impellers provided with vanes generating centrifugal force to achieve the required pressure head.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CENTRIFUGAL PUMP&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;PUMP&gt; in which centrifugal force imparted by impeller is convered to pressure in the volute casing. NOTE - Combine with either  BARE PUMP or PUMP SYSTEM,</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A dynamic pump that contains impellers provided with vanes to generate centrifugal force to achieve the required pressure head.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b435"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000072"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b436"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive classification based on physical mechanism. Under Open World Assumption, any equipment with centrifugal impellers and volute casing could be inferred as a standard centrifugal pump, potentially misclassifying specialized hybrid equipment or complex pump systems that contain centrifugal stages but serve different operational roles.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/VisualInspectionFunction">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">visual inspection function</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de inspeção visual</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000029"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2963"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2964"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in a VisualInspectionProcess and that consists in enabling direct optical observation of internal conditions, fluid properties, or process states within containers, vessels, or piping systems for operational monitoring, safety verification, or maintenance purposes.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
  </rdf:Description>
