  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000308">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">knock out drum</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">vaso separador de condensado</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A knock out drum is a separator designed to separate relatively small quantities of liquid from a vapor stream through gravitational and momentum-based phase separation.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um vaso separador de condensado é um separador projetado para separar quantidades relativamente pequenas de líquido de uma corrente de vapor através de separação de fases gravitacional e baseada em momento.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every knock out drum is a separator that bears a knock out separation function, which is realized in processes that separate small quantities of liquid from vapor streams.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A drum intended to separate relatively small quantities of liquid from a vapour stream.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;KNOCK OUT DRUM&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;VESSEL&gt; and a &lt;VAPOUR-LIQUID SEPATATOR&gt; intended to separate relatively small quantities of liquid from a vapour stream</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A drum intended to separate relatively small quantities of liquid from a vapour stream</skos:definition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2057"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(KnockOutDrum(x) ↔ Separator(x) ∧ ∃f(KnockOutSeparationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b89">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ThermalEnergyPortion"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasInput"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b701">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FluidPathway"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000209">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b82"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b81"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b83"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b80"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000092"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um trocador de calor resfriado a ar é um trocador de calor que possui superfícies aletadas de resfriamento a ar e usa ar ambiente como meio de resfriamento para transferir energia térmica de fluidos de processo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An air cooled heat exchanger is a heat exchanger that has finned air cooling surfaces and uses ambient air as the cooling medium to transfer thermal energy from process fluids.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;AIR COOLED HEAT EXCHANGER&gt; is a &lt;HEAT EXCHANGER&gt; and an &lt;AIR COOLED OBJECT&gt; and a &lt;FLUID CONTAINER&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A cooler that is intended to use air as the cooling medium.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A cooler that is intended to use air as the cooling medium.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every air cooled heat exchanger is a heat exchanger that has component parts including an air fin system and tube bundle, and participates in air cooling processes.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">air cooled heat exchanger</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">trocador de calor resfriado a ar</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(AirCooledHeatExchanger(x) → HeatExchanger(x) ∧ ∃y(AirFinSystem(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y)) ∧ ∃z(TubeBundle(z) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,z)) ∧ ∃p(AirCoolingProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Under the Open World Assumption, defining air cooling constructively as sufficient conditions could lead to false positives. Complex hybrid equipment or specialized configurations with air cooling components might be inappropriately classified. Starting with necessary conditions allows for proper validation by domain experts before upgrading to equivalence.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
