  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000316">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">bocal</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">nozzle</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Nozzle(x) ↔ MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃f(FluidDirectionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃o(ShapedOrifice(o) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,o)) ∧ ∃p(ProtrudingPart(p) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that has a protruding part through which a stream of fluid is directed.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A physical object that has a protruding part through which a stream of fluid is directed.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A shaped orifice for directing fluid flow.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[DEXPI] A projecting short piece of pipe that is attached to another (hollow) body.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;NOZZLE&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;FLUID PORT&gt; and a &lt;CONNECTOR&gt; that is a protruding part through which a stream of fluid is directed</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every nozzle is a material artifact that bears a fluid direction function and has a shaped orifice and protruding part as component parts.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A nozzle is a material artifact that has a protruding part with a shaped orifice designed to direct fluid flow into a specific pattern.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um bocal é um artefato material que possui uma parte protuberante com um orifício moldado projetado para direcionar o fluxo de fluido em um padrão específico.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2286"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000334">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A pressure indicating transmitter is a transmitter that measures pressure and provides both local visual indication and electrical signal transmission of the pressure value.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um transmissor indicador de pressão é um transmissor que mede pressão e fornece tanto indicação visual local quanto transmissão de sinal elétrico do valor da pressão.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pressure indicating transmitter</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">transmissor indicador de pressão</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every pressure indicating transmitter is a transmitter that bears a pressure indicating and transmission function, has pressure signal as input, and has both electrical signal output and local pressure display.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[isa5_1] ISA 5.1 tag abbreviation 'PIT'. First letter 'P': Pressure. Succeeding letters: 'I' = Indicate, 'T' = Transmit.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (PressureIndicatingTransmitter(x) ↔ Transmitter(x) ∧ ∃f(PressureIndicatingAndTransmissionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃i(PressureSignal(i) ∧ hasInput(x,i)) ∧ ∃o1(ElectricalSignal(o1) ∧ hasOutput(x,o1)) ∧ ∃o2(LocalPressureDisplay(o2) ∧ hasOutput(x,o2)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2631"/>
  </rdf:Description>
