  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2322">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PowerTransmissionProcess"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000108">
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A diaphragm valve is a valve that uses a resilient diaphragm forced against a port as its closure mechanism to control fluid flow.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula de diafragma é uma válvula que usa um diafragma resiliente forçado contra uma porta como seu mecanismo de fechamento para controlar o fluxo de fluido.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Since this is a constructive type defined by physical mechanism (diaphragm closure), necessary conditions are used to avoid over-classification under the Open World Assumption. Not every equipment with a diaphragm component should automatically be classified as a diaphragm valve - the structural differentia requires domain validation.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000077"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b951"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b950"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b949"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">diaphragm valve</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula de diafragma</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (DiaphragmValve(x) → Valve(x) ∧ ∃d,p (ResilientDiaphragm(d) ∧ Port(p) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,d) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every diaphragm valve is a valve that has a resilient diaphragm as component part and has a port as component part and participates in diaphragm closure processes.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DIAPHRAGM VALVE&gt; is a &lt;MEMBRANE VALVE&gt; where the closure member is a resilient diaphragm being forced against a port</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A membrane valve that is a membrane valve where the closure member is a resilient diaphragm being forced against a port.</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2717">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#AllDisjointClasses"/>
    <owl:members rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2718"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000143">
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (PressureGauge(x) ↔ (Instrument(x) ∧ ∃f (PressureMeasurementFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">manômetro</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pressure gauge</rdfs:label>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2617"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every pressure gauge is an instrument that has the function to measure and display pressure</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A 'pressure measuring gauge' intended to measure and display a representation of a measured pressure</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A gauge intended to measure and display a representation of a measured pressure.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A device used to measure pressure.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;PRESSURE GAUGE&gt; is a &lt;PROCESS GAUGE&gt; and a &lt;PRESSURE MEASURING INSTRUMENT&gt; using a &lt;PRESSURE MEASURING ELEMENT&gt;</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A pressure gauge is an indicator that bears the function of measuring and displaying pressure values.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um manômetro é um indicador que possui a função de medir e exibir valores de pressão.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2741">
