  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1753">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasSpecifiedOutput"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FluidPortion"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000252">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">differential pressure switch</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">interruptor de pressão diferencial</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A pilot switch intended to switch or give an on/off signal when the measured differential pressure has reached a pre-set value.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DIFFERENTIAL PRESSURE SWITCH&gt; is a &lt;PRESSURE SWITCH&gt; and a &lt;DIFFERENTIAL PRESSURE MEASURING INSTRUMENT&gt;</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(DifferentialPressureSwitch(x) ↔ PressureSwitch(x) ∧ ∃f(DifferentialPressureSwitchingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every differential pressure switch is a pressure switch that has the function to switch based on differential pressure measurements between two pressure inputs.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1003"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um interruptor de pressão diferencial é um interruptor de pressão que possui uma função de comutação de pressão diferencial para comutar ou fornecer sinais liga/desliga quando a pressão diferencial medida entre duas entradas atinge um valor pré-estabelecido.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A differential pressure switch is a pressure switch that bears a differential pressure switching function to switch or provide on/off signals when the measured differential pressure between two inputs reaches a pre-set value.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000290">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1737"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000121"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">roda dentada</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">gear wheel</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(GearWheel(x) → Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(PowerTransmissionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃t(Tooth(t) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,t)) ∧ ∃w(WheelBody(w) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,w)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive differentia based on physical structure (toothed geometry). Under OWA, asserting equivalence could force classification of complex hybrid mechanisms or specialized toothed components that should not be categorized as standard gear wheels for maintenance purposes.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;GEAR WHEEL&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;TRANSMITTER(force)&gt; and that is a toothed wheel usend in conjunction with another, or with a rack, to transmit motion</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">GearWheel SubClassOf Assembly and (bearerOf some PowerTransmissionFunction) and (hasComponentPartAtAllTimes some Tooth) and (hasComponentPartAtAllTimes some WheelBody)</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An Assembly that bears a PowerTransmissionFunction and that has circumferential teeth for positive mechanical engagement with mating gears or racks to transmit rotational motion and power.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um Assembly que porta uma PowerTransmissionFunction e que possui dentes circunferenciais para engajamento mecânico positivo com engrenagens ou cremalheiras correspondentes para transmitir movimento rotacional e potência.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
  </rdf:Description>
