  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000286">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;GAS TURBINE&gt; is a &lt;TURBINE&gt; that compresses air which is then mixed with fuel for combustion and expansion through a turbine section to generate relatively high power output for either mechanical drive or power generation</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A turbine that compresses air which is then mixed with fuel for combustion and expansion through a turbine section to generate relatively high power output for either mechanical drive or power generation.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A turbine that compresses air which is then mixed with fuel for combustion and expansion through a turbine section to generate relatively high power output for either mechanical drive or power generation.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(GasTurbine(x) ↔ Turbine(x) ∧ ∃c,h(Compressor(c) ∧ CombustionChamber(h) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,c) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,h)) ∧ ∃p1,p2(AirCompressionProcess(p1) ∧ FuelCombustionProcess(p2) ∧ participatesIn(x,p1) ∧ participatesIn(x,p2)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma turbina a gás é uma turbina que possui um compressor e câmara de combustão integrados, projetada para comprimir ar ambiente, misturá-lo com combustível para combustão, e expandir os gases quentes resultantes através de uma seção de turbina para gerar energia mecânica.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A gas turbine is a turbine that has an integrated compressor and combustion chamber, designed to compress ambient air, mix it with fuel for combustion, and expand the resulting hot gases through a turbine section to generate mechanical power.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every gas turbine is a turbine that has component parts compressor and combustion chamber at all times, and participates in air compression process and fuel combustion process.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">turbina a gás</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">gas turbine</rdfs:label>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1666"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b950">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000329"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1727">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000335"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000296">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;HOSE&gt; is a &lt;TUBULAR&gt; that is flexible and capable of conducting liquids under pressure</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A tubular which is flexible and capable of conveying liquids under pressure.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A tubular which is flexible and capable of conveying liquids under pressure.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Hose(x) → Pipe(x) ∧ ∃q(Flexibility(q) ∧ hasQuality(x,q)) ∧ ∃c(PressurizedFluidConduction(c) ∧ capableOf(x,c)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A hose is a flexible pipe designed to conduct liquids under pressure while accommodating positional movement and bending.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma mangueira é um tubo flexível projetado para conduzir líquidos sob pressão enquanto acomoda movimento posicional e flexão.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions because this is a constructive type defined by physical properties (flexibility). Under OWA, asserting equivalence would force any artifact with flexibility and pressure capability to be classified as a hose, potentially including complex equipment with flexible components that should not be categorized as standard hoses.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000321"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1855"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1856"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1857"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1858"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">hose</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">mangueira</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every hose is a pipe that has flexibility and is capable of conducting liquids under pressure.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
