  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000373">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma FiatObjectPart que é parte de um vaso e que fecha o casco do vaso fornecendo uma fronteira terminal para contenção.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A FiatObjectPart that is part of a vessel and that closes a vessel shell by providing an end boundary for containment.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;VESSEL HEAD&gt; is an &lt;EQUIPMENT COMPONENT&gt; that is intended to close a vessel shell.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(VesselHead(x) → FiatObjectPart(x) ∧ ∃y(Vessel(y) ∧ partOf(x,y)) ∧ ∃r(VesselClosureRole(r) ∧ realizes(x,r)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every vessel head is a fiat object part that is part of some vessel and realizes a vessel closure role.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b3416"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type based on structural configuration. Under OWA, asserting sufficient conditions for vessel head closure would inappropriately classify any part that closes a vessel (including specialized manifolds, complex multi-port heads, or custom closures) as standard vessel heads, potentially creating false positives in maintenance categorization.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">vessel head</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">tampo de vaso</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/MaterialProcessingFunction">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2220"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2221"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/DesignedFunction"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">material processing function</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de processamento de material</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000118">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[isa5_1] ISA 5.1 tag abbreviation 'FT'. First letter 'F': Flow, Flow Rate. Succeeding letters: 'T' = Transmit.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A flow transmitter providing an output signal that is proportional to the flow inputs from a flow element.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A transmitter that is producing a standardized output signal dependent of a received input signal from a flow sensor.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FLOW TRANSMITTER&gt; is a &lt;PROCESS VARIABLE TRANSMITTER&gt; and a &lt;FLOW MEASURING INSTRUMENT&gt;</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every flow transmitter is a transmitter that has the function of transmitting flow signals and has as input flow measurements.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">transmissor de fluxo</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flow transmitter</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um transmissor de fluxo é um transmissor que produz sinais de saída padronizados proporcionais às medições de fluxo provenientes de elementos sensores de fluxo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A flow transmitter is a transmitter that produces standardized output signals proportional to flow measurements from flow sensing elements.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1564"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (FlowTransmitter(x) ↔ Transmitter(x) ∧ ∃f(FlowSignalTransmissionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃m(FlowMeasurement(m) ∧ hasInput(x,m)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/MultiServiceTransmissionProcess">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b3315"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b3313"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b3314"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b3312"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de transmissão de múltiplos serviços</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">multi service transmission process</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000207">
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every actuator is an assembly that has the function of converting external energy into controlled kinetic motion.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000207"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b49"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object for changing a signal into a corresponding movement.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A transducer that is intended to convert energy (electric, mechanical, pneumatic or hydraulic) from an external source into kinetic energy (motion) in response to a signal or or power input.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] An actuator is a type of motor for moving or controlling a mechanism or system. Actuator's are a vital part of offshore operations.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;ACTUATOR&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that is capable of &lt;ACTUATING&gt;</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um atuador é um conjunto que possui uma função de atuação para converter energia de uma fonte externa em movimento cinético em resposta a sinais de controle.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An actuator is an assembly that bears an actuation function to convert energy from an external source into kinetic motion in response to control signals.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">actuator</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">atuador</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Actuator(x) ↔ Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f (ActuationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PressureReliefProcess">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2796"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
