  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000321">
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every pipe is a material artifact that has fluid conduction function and has tubular geometry and has longitudinal extent.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2406"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2407"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2405"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pipe</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">tubo</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Pipe(x) → MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃f(FluidConductionFunction(f) ∧ hasFunction(x,f)) ∧ ∃g(TubularGeometry(g) ∧ hasPhysicalProperty(x,g)) ∧ ∃h(LongitudinalExtent(h) ∧ hasPhysicalProperty(x,h)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] An 'artefact' that is a long tube or hollow body intended for conduction of liquid, gaseous or finely divided solid materials, or used for structural purposes.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;PIPE&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;FLUID CONDUCTOR&gt; that is a long tube or hollow body intended for conduction of liquid, gaseous or finely divided solid materials, or used for structural purposes</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[DEXPI] An elementary piece of piping, i.e., not interrupted by any item.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that is a long tube or hollow body intended for conduction of liquid, gaseous or finely divided solid materials, or used for structural purposes.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions because pipe is defined by constructive/geometric properties (tubular geometry, longitudinal extent) rather than purely functional criteria. Under Open World Assumption, asserting sufficient conditions based on geometric properties could lead to unintended classification of complex tubular structures that happen to conduct fluids but should not be categorized as standard pipes.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um tubo é um artefato material caracterizado por geometria tubular e extensão longitudinal, projetado para conduzir materiais líquidos, gasosos ou sólidos finamente divididos de um local para outro, ou para servir a propósitos estruturais.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A pipe is a material artifact characterized by tubular geometry and longitudinal extent, designed to conduct liquid, gaseous or finely divided solid materials from one location to another, or to serve structural purposes.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
