  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000105">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">choke valve</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula choke</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula choke é uma válvula que possui uma função de redução de pressão, projetada para reduzir a pressão do fluido da entrada para a saída através de restrição controlada do fluxo e dissipação de energia.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A choke valve is a valve that bears a pressure reduction function, designed to reduce fluid pressure from inlet to outlet through controlled flow restriction and energy dissipation.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b496"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every choke valve is a valve that bears a pressure reduction function and has a flow restriction element as component part at all times.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A valve that can be used to obstruct the fluid passing inside, and has the ability to reduce the pressure from the inlet port to the outlet port.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A valve that can be used to obstruct the fluid passing inside, and has the ability to reduce the pressure from the inlet port to the outlet port.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CHOKE VALVE&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;VALVE&gt; in which a solid cylinder is raised and lowered, and which is placed around or inside another cylinder that has holes or slots. The design of a choke valve means fluids flowing through the cage are coming from all sides and that the streams of flow (through the holes or slots) collide with each other at the center of the cage cylinder, thereby dissipating the energy of the fluid through flow impingement. The main advantage of choke valves is that they can be designed to be totally linear in their flow rate</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (ChokeValve(x) ↔ (Valve(x) ∧ ∃f (PressureReductionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000105"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000351">
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2991"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">silo</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">silo</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SILO&gt; is a &lt;CONTAINER&gt; with a conical shape that is intended to store solids in bulk</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A vessel that has a bottom in the shape of a cone and is intended to store solid particles.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[DEXPI] A with a conical shape that is intended to store solids in bulk (from ``_).</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A silo is a vessel that bears a solid bulk storage function and has a conical bottom section for facilitating the storage and discharge of bulk solid materials.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um silo é um vaso que possui uma função de armazenamento de sólidos a granel e tem uma seção inferior cônica para facilitar o armazenamento e descarga de materiais sólidos a granel.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Silo(x) ↔ (Vessel(x) ∧ ∃f(SolidBulkStorageFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃c(ConicalBottom(c) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,c))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every silo is a vessel that has the function of storing bulk solids and has a conical bottom component.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
