  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000157">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A 'detecting instrument' that generates a process variable signal and converts it into an output signal.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;TRANSMITTER&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that is capable of &lt;TRANSMITTING&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that is an element that receives a process variable signal from a sensor and converts it into an output signal.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[isa5_1] a device that senses a process variable through the medium of a sensor or measuring element and has an output whose steady-state value varies only as a predetermined function of the process variable.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[DEXPI] A detecting instrument that generates a process variable signal and converts it into an output signal.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">transmissor</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">transmitter</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every transmitter is an instrument that has the function of signal transmission and has a sensor element and signal conditioner and transmission module and receives process variable inputs and produces standardized signal outputs.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A transmitter is an instrument that bears a signal transmission function, receiving process variable signals from sensors and converting them into standardized output signals for transmission to control systems.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um transmissor é um instrumento que possui uma função de transmissão de sinal, recebendo sinais de variáveis de processo de sensores e convertendo-os em sinais de saída padronizados para transmissão a sistemas de controle.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b3240"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Transmitter(x) ↔ Instrument(x) ∧ ∃f(SignalTransmissionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃s(SensorElement(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)) ∧ ∃c(SignalConditioner(c) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,c)) ∧ ∃t(TransmissionModule(t) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,t)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2177">
