  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000151">
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every storage tank is a tank that has the function to store materials for extended periods.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;STORAGE TANK&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;TANK&gt; that is intended for storage</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">storage tank</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">tanque de armazenamento</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um tanque de armazenamento é um vaso projetado para armazenar fluidos ou materiais por períodos prolongados sem transformação ou processamento ativo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A storage tank is a vessel that is designed to store fluids or materials for extended periods without transformation or active processing.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:altLabel xml:lang="en">tank</skos:altLabel>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b3055"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(StorageTank(x) ↔ (Tank(x) ∧ ∃f(ExtendedStorageFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000272">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A detector that is intended to sense a flame.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A detector that is intended to sense a flame.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FLAME DETECTOR&gt; is a &lt;DETECTOR&gt; and a &lt;FLAME DETECTING INSTRUMENT&gt; using a &lt;FLAME DETECTING MEASURING ELEMENT&gt; that is designed to detect the presence of a flame</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flame detector</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">detector de chama</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(FlameDetector(x) ↔ Detector(x) ∧ ∃f(FlameDetectionFunction(f) ∧ hasFunction(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A flame detector is a detector that has the function to detect the presence of flames.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um detector de chama é um detector que tem a função de detectar a presença de chamas.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every flame detector is a detector that has a flame detection function, and every detector that has a flame detection function is a flame detector.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1377"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000367">
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Umbilical(x) → Assembly(x) ∧ ∃c,t,s,conn (CableBundle(c) ∧ TubingBundle(t) ∧ ProtectiveSheathing(s) ∧ ConnectorAssembly(conn) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,c) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,t) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,conn) ∧ hasQuality(x,Flexibility) ∧ hasQuality(x,EasyDisconnectability)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b3317"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b3316"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b3319"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b3320"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b3318"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every umbilical is an assembly that has component parts including cable bundles and tubing bundles, and has the qualities of flexibility and easy disconnectability.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A device which is a flexible and easily disconnectable collection of cables and/or tubing for control, power, communication or chemical injection purposes.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;UMBILICAL&gt; is a &lt;DRILLING COMPONENT&gt; that is a flexible and easily disconnectable collection of cables and/or tubing for control, power, communication or chemical injection purposes.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] An assembly of hydraulic hoses which can also include electrical cables or optic fibres, used to control a sub sea structure or remote operated vehicle from a platform or a vessel.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A control line attached to a remove piece of equipment, usually a subsea wellhead, to provide hydraulic or electrical control, or inject small amounts of chemicals.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An umbilical is an assembly that is a flexible and easily disconnectable bundle containing both cables and tubing for multi-service transmission including control, power, communication, and chemical injection.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um umbilical é uma montagem que é um feixe flexível e facilmente desconectável contendo cabos e tubulação para transmissão de múltiplos serviços incluindo controle, energia, comunicação e injeção química.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive basis requires necessary conditions only. Under OWA, any assembly with cables, tubing, flexibility, and disconnectability could be forcibly classified as umbilical, including specialized multi-service bundles, complex wiring harnesses, or custom transmission assemblies that contain these elements but serve different industrial contexts and maintenance categories.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">umbilical</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">umbilical</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1379">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FlameSensingElement"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000320">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">armadilha de pig</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pig trap</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every pig trap is an assembly that bears a pig launching and receiving function and has component parts that are a pig launcher and a pig receiver.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(PigTrap(x) ↔ Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(PigLaunchingAndReceivingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃l(PigLauncher(l) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,l)) ∧ ∃r(PigReceiver(r) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,r)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;PIG TRAP&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;TOOL&gt; that is a pipeline maintenance tool, which includes a launcher and receiver, introducing a &lt;PIPE PIG&gt; into the line</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A facility on a pipeline for inserting and retrieving a scraper or pig.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] "</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma armadilha de pig é um conjunto que possui a função de lançar e receber pigs de tubulação para manutenção de dutos e possui componentes de lançador e receptor.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A pig trap is an assembly that bears the function of launching and receiving pipe pigs for pipeline maintenance and has both launcher and receiver components.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2382"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1862">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasSpecifiedOutput"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000112">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DOWN HOLE SAFETY VALVE&gt; is a &lt;SAFETY VALVE&gt; that is intended for subsurface control/check operation</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A valve that is intended for subsurface control/check operation.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A down hole safety valve is a safety valve that bears a subsurface safety function for pressure relief and flow control operations in wellbore or other subsurface environments.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula de segurança de fundo de poço é uma válvula de segurança que possui uma função de segurança subsuperficial para operações de alívio de pressão e controle de fluxo em poços ou outros ambientes subsuperficiais.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">down hole safety valve</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula de segurança de fundo de poço</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every down hole safety valve is a safety valve that bears a SubsurfaceSafetyFunction and participates in SubsurfaceOperationProcess</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1094"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(DownHoleSafetyValve(x) ↔ SafetyValve(x) ∧ ∃f(SubsurfaceSafetyFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃p(SubsurfaceOperationProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1510">
    <owl:intersectionOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1512"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b527">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasInput"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ProcessFluidSample"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000364">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A device attached to the topmost tubing joint in the wellhead to support the tubing string.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A slip set or donut that suspends and holds the top of the tubing in the wellhead.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A well string hanger that is used for production tubing. The tubing hanger incorporates a sealing system to ensure that the tubing conduit and annulus are hydraulically isolated.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;TUBING HANGER&gt; is a &lt;WELL STRING HANGER&gt; that is installed on top of the tubing string and supports the string when landed in the tubing hanger or tubing head.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">tubing hanger</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">suporte de coluna de produção</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every tubing hanger is an assembly that bears a tubing support function and has component parts including a sealing system, support mechanism, and tubing connection.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A tubing hanger is an assembly that supports tubing strings in wellheads with integrated sealing to isolate tubing conduit from annulus.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um suporte de coluna de produção é um conjunto que suporta colunas de produção em cabeças de poço com vedação integrada para isolar o conduto da coluna do anular.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b3256"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(TubingHanger(x) ↔ (Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(TubingSupportFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃s(SealingSystem(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)) ∧ ∃m(SupportMechanism(m) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,m)) ∧ ∃c(TubingConnection(c) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,c))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
