  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000235">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A heat exchanger that is intended to cool a physical object.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;COOLER&gt; is a &lt;HEAT EXCHANGER&gt; that has a capability of &lt;COOLING&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A heat exchanger that is intended to cool a physical object.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A cooler is a heat exchanger that bears a CoolingFunction.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um resfriador é um trocador de calor que possui uma FunçãoDeResfriamento.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Cooler(x) ↔ HeatExchanger(x) ∧ ∃f (CoolingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b698"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">cooler</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">resfriador</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every cooler is a heat exchanger that has the function of cooling.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000300">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">bomba hidráulica</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">hydraulic pump</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;HYDRAULIC PUMP&gt; is a &lt;POSITIVE DISPLACEMENT PUMP&gt; used in hydraulic drive systems and can be hydrostatic or hydrodynamic. It is a mechanical source of power that converts mechanical power into hydraulic energy (hydrostatic energy i.e. flow, pressure). It generates flow with enough power to overcome pressure induced by the load at the pump outlet. When a hydraulic pump operates, creates a vacuum at the pump inlet, which forces liquid from the reservoir into the inlet line to the pump and by mechanical action delivers this liquid to the pump outlet and forces it into the hydraulic system.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] An artificial lift system that is powered by injected fluid (usually water), that powers a pump similar to the rotating pump used in electrical submersible pumps.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A hydraulic pump is a positive displacement pump that converts mechanical power into hydraulic energy for hydraulic drive systems.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma bomba hidráulica é uma bomba de deslocamento positivo que converte energia mecânica em energia hidráulica para sistemas de acionamento hidráulico.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1917"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every hydraulic pump is a positive displacement pump that bears a hydraulic pumping function and participates in hydraulic power transmission processes.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (HydraulicPump(x) ↔ PositiveDisplacementPump(x) ∧ ∃f(HydraulicPumpingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃p(HydraulicPowerTransmissionProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000237">
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(CoriolisMassFlowMeter(x) → FlowMeter(x) ∧ ∃y(CoriolisFlowTube(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y)) ∧ ∃z(CoriolisPrinciple(z) ∧ utilizesPhysicalPrinciple(x,z)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b738"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b742"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b740"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b741"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000278"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b739"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every coriolis mass flow meter is a flow meter that has component part at all times some Coriolis flow tube and utilizes the Coriolis principle.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A mass flow meter that uses the Coriolis principle to measure a mass flow rate through the meter.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A mass flow meter that uses the Coriolis principle to measure a mass flow rate through the meter.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions for this constructive type. Under the Open World Assumption, defining sufficient conditions based on Coriolis principle usage could lead to false positives where other devices using Coriolis forces (like gyroscopes or accelerometers) might be incorrectly classified as flow meters. The structural differentia provides necessary conditions that can be validated by domain experts.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A flow meter that utilizes the Coriolis principle through specialized oscillating flow tubes to directly measure mass flow rate of fluids.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um medidor de vazão que utiliza o princípio de Coriolis através de tubos de fluxo oscilantes especializados para medir diretamente a vazão mássica de fluidos.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">coriolis mass flow meter</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">medidor de vazão Coriolis</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
