    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1365"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2639">
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2633"/>
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2640"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000342">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">rotor</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">rotor</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An Assembly that participates in rotational motion and has a rotor shaft as an essential component, designed to transfer mechanical energy through rotational motion within a machine assembly.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um Assembly que participa em movimento rotacional e tem um eixo do rotor como componente essencial, projetado para transferir energia mecânica através de movimento rotacional dentro de um conjunto de máquina.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2792"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Rotor(x) → Assembly(x) ∧ ∃p(RotationalMotionProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)) ∧ ∃s(RotorShaft(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every Rotor is an Assembly that participates in some RotationalMotionProcess and has some rotor shaft as component part at all times.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;ROTOR&gt; is a &lt;MACHINE COMPONENT&gt; that is the rotating portion of a machine</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] The rotating shaft in a PDM motor.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">As a constructive type defined by physical configuration (rotating portion with shaft), providing sufficient conditions under OWA could lead to overclassification. Complex assemblies containing rotating elements might be incorrectly classified as rotors rather than their proper categories (motors, compressors, etc.).</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1597">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:intersectionOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1601"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000289">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;GEAR PUMP&gt; is a &lt;ROTARY PUMP&gt; that contains gear teeth within an casing or enclosure to transport liquid at relatively high back pressures</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A rotary pump that contains gear teeth within an casing or enclosure to transport liquid at relatively high back pressures and by which gear meshing serves as reverse flow seal.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">bomba de engrenagem</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">gear pump</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000072"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1726"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1728"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1729"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1727"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1725"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every gear pump is a pump that has as component part at all times a gear mechanism and a pump casing, and bears a pumping function.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A gear pump is a pump that contains gear teeth within a casing or enclosure to transport liquid at relatively high back pressures through meshing action.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma bomba de engrenagem é uma bomba que contém dentes de engrenagem dentro de um invólucro ou carcaça para transportar líquido em pressões de retorno relativamente altas através de ação de engrenamento.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions for this constructive type. While the gear mechanism is definitionally necessary for gear pumps, making it sufficient under OWA could lead to false positives - any complex equipment containing gears (like gearboxes with integrated pumps or multi-function units) might be incorrectly classified as standard gear pumps for maintenance purposes.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (GearPump(x) → Pump(x) ∧ ∃g,c (GearMechanism(g) ∧ PumpCasing(c) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,g) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,c)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
