  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000341">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">bomba rotativa</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">rotary pump</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2784"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2783"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2781"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2782"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000331"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A positive displacement pump that consists of a chamber containing gears, cams, screws, vanes, plungers or similar elements actuated by relative rotation of the drive shaft or casing and which has no separate inlet and outlet valves.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;ROTARY PUMP&gt; is a &lt;POSITIVE DISPLACEMENT PUMP&gt; that consists of a chamber containing gears, cams, screws, vanes, plungers or similar elements actuated by relative rotation of the drive shaft or casing and which has no separate inlet and outlet valves.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A positive displacement pump that consists of a chamber containing gears, cams, screws, vanes, plungers or similar elements actuated by relative rotation of the drive shaft or casing and which has no separate inlet and outlet valves.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions for this constructive type. While the rotary mechanism is clearly necessary for rotary pumps, making it sufficient under OWA could lead to false positives where complex equipment containing rotary elements (like gearboxes with pumping side-effects or hybrid machines) might be misclassified as standard rotary pumps. The constructive differentia should be validated by domain experts before upgrading to equivalence.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma bomba rotativa é uma bomba de deslocamento positivo que contém uma câmara com engrenagens, cames, parafusos, palhetas, êmbolos ou elementos similares acionados pela rotação relativa do eixo de acionamento ou carcaça, e que não possui válvulas separadas de entrada e saída.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A rotary pump is a positive displacement pump that contains a chamber with gears, cams, screws, vanes, plungers or similar elements actuated by relative rotation of the drive shaft or casing, and which has no separate inlet and outlet valves.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (RotaryPump(x) → PositiveDisplacementPump(x) ∧ ∃y (RotaryDisplacementMechanism(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y)) ∧ ¬∃z (SeparateInletValve(z) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,z)) ∧ ¬∃w (SeparateOutletValve(w) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,w)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every rotary pump is a positive displacement pump that has a rotary displacement mechanism as component part and lacks separate inlet and outlet valves.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000370">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um MaterialArtifact que é uma parte componente de uma válvula e que é posicionado no fluxo para permitir, obstruir, desviar ou regular o fluxo através de posicionamento mecânico.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A MaterialArtifact that is a component part of a valve and that is positioned in the flow stream to permit, obstruct, divert or regulate flow through mechanical positioning.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">membro de fechamento de válvula</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">valve closure member</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b3380"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (ValveClosureMember(x) → MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃v (Valve(v) ∧ isComponentPartOf(x,v)) ∧ ∃p (FlowControlProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)) ∧ ∃q (PositionableInFlowStream(q) ∧ hasQuality(x,q)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">As a constructive type defined by physical configuration and mechanical role, the valve closure member should use necessary conditions. The structural differentia (being positioned in flow stream) is harder to make sufficient under OWA - other components or hybrid devices might satisfy the conditions but not be classified as standard valve closure members.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every valve closure member is a material artifact that is a component part of some valve and participates in flow control processes by being positioned within the flow stream.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;VALVE CLOSURE MEMBER&gt; is a &lt;CLOSURE&gt; that is the part of a valve which is positioned in the flow stream to permit, obstruct, divert or regulate flow</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
