  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000374">
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">parte de objeto por fiat</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">vessel shell</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">VesselShell SubClassOf: FiatObjectPart and partOf some Vessel and bearerOf some PressureContainmentFunction</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A fiat object part that is the outer pressure-containing structural boundary of a vessel, designed to enclose and isolate internal contents while withstanding internal pressure loads.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma parte de objeto por fiat que é o limite estrutural externo de contenção de pressão de um vaso, projetada para encerrar e isolar o conteúdo interno enquanto suporta cargas de pressão interna.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(VesselShell(x) → FiatObjectPart(x) ∧ ∃y(Vessel(y) ∧ partOf(x,y)) ∧ ∃f(PressureContainmentFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type defined by structural configuration as outer pressure-containing part of vessel. Under Open World Assumption, sufficient conditions are difficult to establish - other structural components might also be pressure-containing parts of vessels in specialized designs.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b3421"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;VESSEL SHELL&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;SHELL(structure)&gt; that is all or part of the pressure containing outer part of a vessel</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/CylindricalChamber">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">cylindrical chamber</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">câmara cilíndrico</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000107">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A coalescer is a separator that uses coalescence media to promote droplet merger in immiscible liquid mixtures, enabling gravity-based separation where the less dense liquid phase can be skimmed off.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um coalescedor é um separador que usa meio de coalescência para promover a fusão de gotículas em misturas líquidas imiscíveis, permitindo separação por gravidade onde a fase líquida menos densa pode ser removida por escumação.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A gravity separator where two liquid substances separates and where the substance with the less gravity can be skimmed off.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A gravity separator where two liquid substances separates and where the substance with the less gravity can be skimmed off.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;COALESCER&gt; is a &lt;GRAVITY SEPARATOR&gt; where two liquid substances separates and where the substance with the less gravity can be skimmed off.</skos:definition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b576"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">coalescer</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">coalescedor</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Coalescer(x) ↔ (Separator(x) ∧ ∃f(CoalescenceFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃p(GravitySeparationProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)) ∧ ∃o(SkimmableLiquidPortion(o) ∧ hasOutput(x,o))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every coalescer is a separator that bears a coalescence function and participates in gravity separation processes to produce skimmable liquid portions.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1228">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/AirPortion"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasInput"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b520">
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b521"/>
    <rdf:first rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000228"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000353">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000207"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b3015"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000260"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every solenoid actuator is an electric actuator that has a solenoid as component part and has a plunger as component part and converts electrical power to linear mechanical motion.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A solenoid actuator is an electric actuator that utilizes a continuous duty linear solenoid to convert electrical energy into mechanical power via a plunger with an axial stroke in either a push or pull action.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um atuador solenoide é um atuador elétrico que utiliza um solenoide linear de serviço contínuo para converter energia elétrica em energia mecânica através de um êmbolo com curso axial em ação de empurrar ou puxar.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">solenoid actuator</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">atuador solenoide</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SOLENOID ACTUATOR&gt; is an &lt;ELECTRIC ACTUATOR&gt; and an &lt;ELECTRIC TO MECHANICAL ENERGY CONVERTER&gt; and an &lt;ELECTROMECHANICAL DEVICE&gt;  that is utilizing a continuous duty linear solenoid to convert electrical energy into mechanical power via a plunger with an axial stroke in either a push or pull action</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type defined by solenoid mechanism. Under OWA, sufficient conditions would force any device with solenoid and plunger components to be classified as a solenoid actuator, potentially misclassifying complex hybrid devices or specialized equipment containing solenoid components but serving different primary functions.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(SolenoidActuator(x) → ElectricActuator(x) ∧ ∃s(Solenoid(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)) ∧ ∃p(Plunger(p) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000258">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DRYER&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that has a capability of &lt;DRYING&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[DEXPI] An object that has the capability of drying (from ``_).</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">dryer</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">secador</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um secador é um conjunto que possui uma função de secagem para remover umidade de materiais.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A dryer is an assembly that bears a drying function to remove moisture from materials.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1117"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every dryer is an assembly that has the function of drying materials by removing moisture.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Dryer(x) ↔ Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(DryingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2084">
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2085"/>
