  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000132">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A limit switch is an instrument that bears a position limit detection function, mechanically actuated by object motion to provide electrical switching signals when predetermined position limits are reached.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um limit switch é um instrumento que possui uma função de detecção de limite de posição, acionado mecanicamente pelo movimento de objetos para fornecer sinais de chaveamento elétrico quando limites de posição predeterminados são atingidos.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2161"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (LimitSwitch(x) ↔ Instrument(x) ∧ ∃f(PositionLimitDetectionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃p(MechanicalMotion(p) ∧ hasInput(x,p)) ∧ ∃s(ElectricalSignal(s) ∧ hasOutput(x,s)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every limit switch is an instrument that has the function to detect position limits and is mechanically operated by object motion to generate electrical switching signals.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;LIMIT SWITCH&gt; is an &lt;INSTRUMENTATION ITEM&gt; and a &lt;POSITION SWITCH&gt; that is a switch preventing the travel of an object in a mechanism past some predetermined point, mechanically operated by the motion of the object itself</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A position switch having a positive opening operation.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">limit switch</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">limit switch</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
