  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000313">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A cutting tool used to grind up metal, dress off a fish, or open up a window for a kick-off.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;MILL&gt; is a &lt;FACILITY&gt; that consists of the land, buildings, machinery, apparatus, and fixtures, mostly employed in &lt;MANUFACTURING&gt; of discrete &lt;COMMODITY MATERIAL&gt;s</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A mill is usually used to remove junk in the hole or to grind away all or part of a casing string.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Mill(x) ↔ (Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(MaterialProcessingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A mill is an assembly that bears a material processing function to reduce particle size or modify solid materials through mechanical grinding, cutting, or crushing operations.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um moinho é um conjunto que possui uma função de processamento de material para reduzir o tamanho de partículas ou modificar materiais sólidos através de operações mecânicas de moagem, corte ou trituração.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">moinho</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">mill</rdfs:label>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2224"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every mill is an assembly that has the function to process materials, and every assembly that has the function to process materials is a mill.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
