  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000350">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um silenciador é uma montagem que possui a função projetada de reduzir níveis de ruído através do tratamento acústico de fluxos de fluidos.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A silencer is an assembly that bears the designed function of reducing noise levels through acoustic treatment of fluid streams.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object intended to reduce a noise level.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SILENCER&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that has a capability of &lt;SILENCING&gt;</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">silencer</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">silenciador</rdfs:label>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2975"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every silencer is an assembly that has the function to silence noise, and every assembly that has the function to silence noise is a silencer.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Silencer(x) ↔ Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(NoiseSilencingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000224">
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type defined by structural compatibility. Under OWA, asserting equivalence could force classification of any casing with centrifugal compressor compatibility, including hybrid or specialized equipment that should not be automatically classified as standard centrifugal compressor casings.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000222"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b430"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">centrifugal compressor casing</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">invólucro</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(CentrifugalCompressorCasing(x) → Casing(x) ∧ ∃y(CentrifugalCompressor(y) ∧ intendedFor(x,y)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A casing that is specifically designed and dimensioned for structural compatibility with centrifugal compressor mechanisms, providing enclosure and protection for rotating impellers and associated flow components.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um invólucro que é especificamente projetado e dimensionado para compatibilidade estrutural com mecanismos de compressor centrífugo, fornecendo contenção e proteção para impulsores rotativos e componentes de fluxo associados.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CENTRIFUGAL COMPRESSOR CASING&gt; is a &lt;COMPRESSOR CASING&gt; that is intended to be used for a centrifugal compressor.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every centrifugal compressor casing is a casing that is intended for use with centrifugal compressors</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
