  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000323">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2429"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000321"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2428"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2427"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (PipeElbow(x) → (Pipe(x) ∧ ∃g(CurvedGeometry(g) ∧ hasGeometricProperty(x,g)) ∧ ∃p(DirectionalChangeCapacity(p) ∧ hasProperty(x,p))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A pipe elbow is a pipe that has curved geometry enabling directional changes in pipe runs between 0 and 135 degrees.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um cotovelo de tubulação é uma tubulação que possui geometria curva permitindo mudanças direcionais em trechos de tubulação entre 0 e 135 graus.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every pipe elbow is a pipe that has curved geometry and enables directional change capacity between 0 and 135 degrees.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions for this constructive type protects against false positives under OWA. Any curved piping component would be forcibly classified as a pipe elbow under equivalent axioms, including specialized equipment like coiled tubing, serpentine heat exchanger tubes, or custom manifold sections that contain curved passages but should not be asserted into the standard pipe elbow maintenance category.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pipe elbow</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">cotovelo de tubulação</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;PIPE ELBOW&gt; is a &lt;PIPING COMPONENT&gt; and an &lt;ELBOW&gt; that is intended to make a change in the direction of a pipe run between 0 and 135 degrees</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] An 'elbow' and an 'artefact' that is intended to make a change in the direction of a pipe run between 0 and 135 degrees.</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000145">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula de alívio é uma válvula projetada para abrir automaticamente em um ponto de ajuste de pressão predeterminado para aliviar o excesso de pressão e prevenir níveis de pressão inseguros em um sistema.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A relief valve is a valve that is designed to automatically open at a predetermined pressure setpoint to relieve excess pressure and prevent unsafe pressure levels in a system.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;RELIEF VALVE&gt; is an &lt;INSTRUMENTATION ITEM&gt; and a &lt;PRESSURE RELIEF DEVICE&gt; that is set to open at a certain pressure level to prevent the pressure in a container or system from reaching unsafe levels</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A self operating valve that is set to open at a certain pressure level to prevent the pressure in a container or system from reaching unsafe levels.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A quick-acting, spring-loaded valve that opens to relieve pressure when the pressure exceeds the spring setting.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A self operating valve that is set to open at a certain pressure level to prevent the pressure in a container or system from reaching unsafe levels.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A valve in a pressurized system that is set to open and relieve pressure at a certain pressure level.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (ReliefValve(x) ↔ (Valve(x) ∧ ∃f (PressureReliefFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2742"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every relief valve is a valve that bears a pressure relief function, which realizes a pressure relief process that automatically opens the valve when system pressure exceeds a predetermined setpoint.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula de alívio</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">relief valve</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b3269">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#AllDisjointClasses"/>
    <owl:members rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b3270"/>
  </rdf:Description>
