  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000068">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de transferência de calor</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">heat transfer function</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2953"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1809"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1810"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2480"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1329"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1821"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b74"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2952"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1820"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/DesignedFunction"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1328"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2479"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b75"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in a HeatTransferProcess and that consists in facilitating the transfer of thermal energy between two or more fluid media while maintaining their physical separation.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000135">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An on-off control valve is a control valve that bears a binary flow control function, having only two defined positions: fully open and fully closed.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula de controle liga-desliga é uma válvula de controle que possui uma função de controle de fluxo binária, tendo apenas duas posições definidas: totalmente aberta e totalmente fechada.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula de controle liga-desliga</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">on off control valve</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(OnOffControlValve(x) ↔ ControlValve(x) ∧ ∃f(BinaryFlowControlFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2302"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;ON-OFF CONTROL VALVE&gt; is an &lt;INSTRUMENTATION ITEM&gt; and a &lt;CONTROL VALVE&gt; that only has two defined positions, being fully open and fully closed</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every on-off control valve is a control valve that has a BinaryFlowControlFunction and has component part a BinaryPositioner.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/LoggingData">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">dados de perfilagem</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">logging data</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000299">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;HYDRAULIC MOTOR&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;MOTOR&gt; and a &lt;HYDRAULIC TO ROTATION ENERGY CONVERTER&gt; that is intended to generate power by means of high pressure oil</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A motor that is intended to generate power by means of high pressure oil.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A motor that is intended to generate power by means of high pressure oil.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000315"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1905"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1906"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1908"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1907"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1904"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every hydraulic motor is a motor that has hydraulic fluid input and participates in hydraulic-to-mechanical energy conversion process</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">motor hidráulico</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">hydraulic motor</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A hydraulic motor is a motor that generates mechanical energy by converting high pressure hydraulic oil to rotational motion.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um motor hidráulico é um motor que gera energia mecânica convertendo óleo hidráulico de alta pressão em movimento rotacional.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive classification based on hydraulic mechanism. Under Open World Assumption, any device with hydraulic input might be misclassified as a hydraulic motor without domain expert validation of the complete structural requirements.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(HydraulicMotor(x) → Motor(x) ∧ ∃f,p(HydraulicFluidPortion(f) ∧ hasInput(x,f) ∧ HydraulicToMechanicalEnergyConversionProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000343">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">rupture disc</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">disco de ruptura</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A physical object that is designed to burst at a certain excess pressure. It is part of a rupture disc assembly.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;RUPTURE DISC&gt; is an &lt;INSTRUMENT COMPONENT&gt; and an &lt;OVERPRESSURE PROTECTOR&gt; that is designed to burst at a certain excess pressure. It is a part of &lt;RUPTURE DISC ASSEMBLY&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that is a pressure relieving device designed to burst at a calibrated pressure to prevent pressure in systems or vessels from reaching unsafe levels.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A rupture disc is an instrument that realizes pressure relief through irreversible rupture at a calibrated pressure.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um disco de ruptura é um instrumento que realiza alívio de pressão através de ruptura irreversível em uma pressão calibrada.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (RuptureDisc(x) ↔ Instrument(x) ∧ ∃f(PressureReliefFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃p(IrreversibleRuptureProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)) ∧ ∃q(CalibrationPressure(q) ∧ hasQuality(x,q)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2797"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every rupture disc is an instrument that has the function to relieve pressure and participates in irreversible rupture processes at calibrated pressure thresholds.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b611">
    <owl:members rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b612"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#AllDisjointClasses"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b3061">
    <rdf:first rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000314"/>
    <rdf:rest rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#nil"/>
