  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000090">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A pressure vessel is a vessel that bears a pressure containment function, designed to safely withstand internal and/or external pressure loads.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um vaso de pressão é um vaso que possui uma função de contenção sob pressão, projetado para suportar com segurança cargas de pressão internas e/ou externas.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2674"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pressure vessel</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">vaso de pressão</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (PressureVessel(x) ↔ (Vessel(x) ∧ ∃f (PressureContainmentFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A vessel intended to withstand external and/or internal pressure</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every pressure vessel is a vessel that has a pressure containment function, and every vessel with a pressure containment function is a pressure vessel.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000347">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] Abbreviation for shale shaker, the primary and probably most important device on the rig for removing drilled solids from the mud.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SHAKER&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that has the capability of &lt;SHAKING&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A piece of drilling equipment, usually with a vibrating screen, where drill cuttings are removed from the flowing mud.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every shaker is an assembly that has the capability of shaking and contains a vibration mechanism and a shaking element.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2922"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A shaker is an assembly that bears a shaking function, capable of producing vibrating or oscillating motion for material processing, agitation, or separation.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um agitador é um conjunto que possui uma função de agitação, capaz de produzir movimento vibratório ou oscilatório para processamento, agitação ou separação de materiais.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">agitador</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">shaker</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">Shaker(x) ↔ Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(ShakingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000137">
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every phase sequence meter is an electric measuring instrument that has the function to measure phase sequence and has as input polyphase electrical signals.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(PhaseSequenceMeter(x) ↔ ElectricMeasuringInstrument(x) ∧ ∃f(PhaseSequenceMeasurementFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃s(PolyphaseElectricalSignal(s) ∧ hasInput(x,s)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A phase sequence meter is an electric measuring instrument that bears a phase sequence measurement function to determine and indicate the sequence in which the instantaneous voltages of phase conductors reach their maximum value in a polyphase electrical system.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um medidor de sequência de fases é um instrumento de medição elétrica que possui uma função de medição de sequência de fases para determinar e indicar a sequência na qual as tensões instantâneas dos condutores de fase atingem seu valor máximo em um sistema elétrico polifásico.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2330"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">phase sequence meter</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">medidor de sequência de fases</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;PHASE SEQUENCE METER&gt; is an &lt;ELECTRIC VARIABLE MEASURING INSTRUMENT&gt; that indicates, on a polyphase system, the sequence in which the instantaneous voltage of the phase conductors reach their maximum value</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
