  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000131">
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(LevelTransmitter(x) ↔ (Transmitter(x) ∧ ∃f(LevelMeasurementAndTransmissionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">level transmitter</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">transmissor de nível</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um transmissor de nível é um transmissor que mede o nível (altura) de material líquido ou sólido a granel em um recipiente e produz um sinal elétrico de saída padronizado proporcional ao nível medido.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A level transmitter is a transmitter that measures the level (height) of liquid or bulk solid material in a container and produces a standardized electrical output signal proportional to the measured level.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A transmitter that produces a continuous standardized output signal dependent of a received input signal from a level sensor.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;LEVEL TRANSMITTER&gt; is a &lt;PROCESS VARIABLE TRANSMITTER&gt; and a &lt;LEVEL MEASURING INSTRUMENT&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A transmitter that is producing a continuous standardized output signal dependent of a received input signal from a level sensor.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[isa5_1] ISA 5.1 tag abbreviation 'LT'. First letter 'L': Level. Succeeding letters: 'T' = Transmit.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every level transmitter is a transmitter that bears a LevelMeasurementAndTransmissionFunction</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2144"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b825">
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/DehydrationProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/DrillString">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">coluna de perfuração</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">drill string</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000232">
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Condenser(x) ↔ (HeatExchanger(x) ∧ ∃f(CondensationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um condensador é um trocador de calor que possui uma função projetada para condensar vapor em líquido removendo o calor latente de vaporização.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A condenser is a heat exchanger that bears a designed function to condense vapor to liquid by removing latent heat of vaporization.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b625"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A cooler that is intended to change a vapour to liquid.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CONDENSER&gt; is a &lt;COOLER&gt; that has a capability of  &lt;CONDENSING&gt; a &lt;FLUID&gt; from &lt;VAPOUR&gt; to &lt;LIQUID&gt;</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">condensador</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">condenser</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every condenser is a heat exchanger that bears a condensation function, and every heat exchanger that bears a condensation function is a condenser.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b3133">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000173"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000312">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">ManualActuator is an actuator that has input ManualControlSignal and has output MechanicalPower</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;MANUAL ACTUATOR&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and an &lt;ACTUATOR&gt; which action has to be trigged manually</skos:definition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b2210"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (ManualActuator(x) ↔ Actuator(x) ∧ ∃s(ManualControlSignal(s) ∧ hasInput(x,s)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">atuador manual</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">manual actuator</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A manual actuator is an actuator that converts human-operated control inputs into mechanical movement or force through direct physical operation.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um atuador manual é um atuador que converte entradas de controle operadas por humanos em movimento mecânico ou força através de operação física direta.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n23a17477f6ab465c9b392a22c900a573b1001">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
